		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">The Death of a Legend</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=354970" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote><p>Sega has confermed the rumor of discontinuing their famed Dreamcast. In response to Sony’s Playstation 2, as well as other home gaming systems like the booming 733mhz X-Box, Sega’s 200mhz Dreamcast is just unable to compete. Sega plans to change it's strategy to sell Sega titles to the current footholds in the industry like Playstation and X-Box. Home PC users will also see a little of this change. EverQuest may be meeting some new adversaries to contend with on its home front. <a href=http://www.msnbc.com/news/524046.asp?cp1=1#BODY target=_blank>MSNBC</a> has the unveiling story.</blockquote></p><p></p><p>*edited article 12:30pm PST*
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
