				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				yeah yeah yada yada...the usual &quot;Im a programmer&quot; lie.<BR>
According to the &quot;specs&quot; yes the Xbox &quot;WILL&quot; be a better gaming system than the PS2, just like a year ago according to &quot;the specs&quot; the PS2 was going to be a better system than the PS1...<BR>
And yeah when they &quot;first come out&quot; most gaming consoles will look &amp; play as good if not better than the average PC playing a game that unfortunately has been optimized for a lesser PC.<BR>
Same goes with the PS2 playing a game that was designed for the PS1 , it plays it but does not take advantage of what the PS2 has, does that make the PS2 a lesser machine, NO, it makes the game a lesser game...thats the only real disadvantage of PCs is that the game developers are trying to squeeze as much profit as possible by designing games around PCs that should have been upgraded 3 years ago...<BR>
but still my next PC I have on the drawing board <BR>
will still be a much better gaming machine than the PS2, now if they would just start making games optimized for &quot;gamers&quot; and not the average PC user id be in buisness..<BR>
as far as 'Real world benchmarks&quot; fine the PS2 EE engine did great in the POV, Woot, and the Pentium 4 actually beat the Athalon thunderbird 1.2 in 1 benchmark, woot...but as far as slide the disc into your DVD and start a game on your &quot;monitor&quot; running at 1024x768 not your 380x420 TV, with the options of keyboard &amp; mouse, many dif joysticks, wheels, etc...and hooked up thru a cable modem so you can do what really shines on a PC &quot;multiplayer&quot; games and MMRPGS, there is no comparison, well at least for an adult<BR>
sure &quot;Grand turismo&quot; looks good shame its the one and only PS2 game that does..<BR>
Ive never said the PS2 is a piece of junk, but it has a &quot;game developers&quot; glitch just like a pc does in that 95% of the games made for it are for<BR>
Kids, console games are designed mainly for kids because kids are 95% of the console market..<BR>
Pc games are designed around adults using 2+ year old puters because thats the majority out there...<BR>
If PC game developers would just design games for <BR>
PC gamers ie: most people really into games will have a top o the line PC with the latest GPU.. then this whole conversation would be moot because there would be no comparison (for an adult) bottom line is yeah the PS2 is a hell of a<BR>
&quot;pokemon&quot; machine and the PC game developers need to pull their head outa their greedy arse and make PC games for gamers not the average PC user<BR>
that might play a game once in awhile between speadsheets.<BR>
Within the next 1 1/2 years PCs are going to be a huge part of the overall gaming market largely because of alot of the next generation MMRPGs coming out such as Horizons and the like, everything revolves around money and these games make alot of money for the developers and the trend now finally is to make the game graphics as realistic as possible and you cant do that designing everything around a 2+ year old engine.<BR>
So you can say what you want about the PC but it still outplays the PS2 (for an adult) no matter how you look at it, and within 6 months my PC will look &amp; play better than a PS2, but by Xmas 2002 there will PS3 and we can continue this conversation then. Maybe by then you will grow out of your Pokemon machine and the PC game developers will make PC games for gamers
