				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As far as games go i could care less about POV bench marks...Not to mention the Ps2 used in that test was NOT an off the shelf PS2..<BR>
The Breakdown <BR>
<BR>
 PC                                  PS2  <BR>
CPU  1+ ghz That's 1000Mhz+          300 Mhz  <BR>
Hrmm, does it take a genius to figure out which one of these is better? Remember: Just like a salary, more is always better.  <BR>
Graphics Processor  nVidia GeForce 2 Ultra <BR>
31 mil/sec sustained Polygons  &quot;Graphics Synthesizer 20 mil/sec polygons  <BR>
You know, it's actually pretty close here. In fact, there are some radicals out there that believe the PS2 is faster than the top PC stuff. We'd be worried if there were any games or programmers that could actually use all that power. But guess what? There aren't! Heh. With the way nVidia has been crankin' out chipsets, they'll be doubling their polygon output by this time next year. (actually the NV20 will be well over 40Million/sec double that of ps2) <BR>
Memory  256MB+                   32MB (4MB VRAM)  <BR>
This one is embarrassing, really. There are wristwatches and calculators that have more memory than this. A PC video card has this much memory. Seriously, what were they thinking? We weep for the children.  <BR>
Storage  40GB Hard Drives        8MB Memory Card  <BR>
Memory cards! Neat! You can bring them to school and trade them at recess! Maybe Mommy will give you two -- one with Lara Croft on it and the other with The Rock! Yippee! Oh yeah, for the price of four memory cards, you could also buy a 10-gigabyte hard drive...  <BR>
Connectivity  Cable, Ethernet, DSL, Modem...                           PS2    Nada  <BR>
Nothing like playing Unreal Tournament with four people scrunched around one television. It really gives deathmatching that great community feeling. No one really uses that kooky Innerweb thingie to play multiplayer games, do they? Though you will be able to download all the new maps on the PS... oh wait, no you can't, and the mods are so great... oh wait. We're sure it will be great once they patch the PS2. Oh, wait...  <BR>
Resolution  2000+ by 1000+         PS2 640x480  <BR>
If you are reading this right now, it's because you surfed in on a PC. You know 640x480 is lo-tech -- that's what your parents have their computers display so they don't have to look for their glasses. If someone puts a gun to our heads and makes us use this resolution, we'll use it, but afterwards we want to gouge our eyes out with hot pokers.  <BR>
<BR>
So what does it all mean? Technologically, the PS2 is impressive, at least for the next, say, 10 or 15 minutes. Or in comparison to the PSOne. Or a five-year-old computer. But in the world of graphics and tech, better and faster equals success. And the PS2 is already starting to fall behind.<BR>
<BR>
The Conclusion<BR>
So We Don't Get It. Or Do We?<BR>
<BR>
We won't begrudge them a few points, yeah it's a game system and a DVD player combined. So if you've been too cheap to buy a DVD player, this is probably the way to go, you'll get a free game system with it. But in truth, isn't a PC way more than that? <BR>
<BR>
Just 'cause it's got a Sony label on it doesn't mean that the PS2 is the end-all, be-all of &quot;set top boxes.&quot; Truth is, anything the PS2 can do, a PC can do as well, if not better. Also, it's not like you're going to want to sit in front of the TV and type up papers, read email or browse the web, right? Or play MP3s. Or burn CDs. And you sure as hell can't use a PS2 to get at all the good porn floating around out there, that's for sure. Despite Sony Computer Entertainment's Phil Harrison asserting that the PS2 heralds the &quot;death&quot; of PC gaming, there's a few million people out there waiting for Team Fortress 2, Duke Nukem Forever, Warcraft 3 and dozens of other games that will either debut on the PC or only be playable on our beloved open platform. We can definitely understand the lure of new technology, especially when it comes to games, but you'll never catch us waiting in line for eighteen hours to get our hands on a new 3D accelerator or CPU.<BR>
<BR>
This whole Rant was not from me but from Dailyradar but i pretty much agree with it..<BR>
The ps2 will not compete with a pc.<BR>

