				well I dont think the consoles suck but for the most part they dont really compare to a PC...<BR>
Even the Xbox would barely run a game like Horizons where the minimum req are a 700mhz p111 with 128 MB ram...The main problem with PCs right now is the fact that most companies putting games out are making them for the average PC of 2 years ago ie: P11 200-300mhz with 32 mb ram, most true PC &quot;gamers&quot; right now Im sure have a much better system than that and would gladly upgrade to a Gig+ chip and 64mb video card if more games were<BR>
designed to take advantage of those reqs...<BR>
By next year if you dont have a 1+Gig processor<BR>
min of 128 DDR ram and a NV20 video card then your not even going to be able to play the newest PC games coming out in 2002, because im sure alot of games are going to go the route of Horizons.<BR>
Im going to start building my next puter in about 3 months when the new DDR mother boards will be out<BR>
and hopefully with the USB 2.0 on them. I may wait longer maybe til Oct-Nov when the 1.7Gig Athalon palomino comes out.<BR>
Eventhough everybody says a puter is upgradable and a console isnt, thats true but only to a small degree, I mean yes you CAN upgrade your video card, sound card but if your running a p11 233mhz then a 64 mb Geforce ultra or NV20 is going to do you no good at all, so in all reallity you basically do the same as most console owners and buy a new puter every 3 years.<BR>
I think the 1.7 gig Athalon with 256 DDR 333-400 mhz ram a NV20 Vcard with a few assorted other goodies should do me til about 2003-04, then rinse and repeat...<BR>
The best thing about the consoles is that the games are uptimized for that exact system the programers know exactly what they have to work with and push the game to the limits of that box.<BR>
I wish PC games could come out with different versions of a game one optimized for a top o the line system and 1 for a dog...<BR>
Even though the Reqs for Horizons sounds a bit high to most, a 700mhz+ with 128 mB sdram in summer of 2002 WILL be a dog..<BR>
IF programers of PC games could design games to take advantage of the power of the top 1/2 of PC users instead of the bottom 1/2 then there would be no comparison to a console, the PC would be way better. The good thing is with the Xbox coming out alot of PC game programmers are going to have to optimize the 2002 games to a min of 800mhz+ to compete :)....<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
</table><br>
